# vfs_bind: register two FSProviders rooted in different
# subdirectories (p1, p2), bind p2 BEFORE p1 at the root, exercise
# UNION-aware walk: first-found / fallback-to-second / both-notfound,
# then cache-hit on a repeat walk. `{ROOT}` is template-substituted
# by the test runner before the binary is invoked.
#
# Coverage:
#   - bindroot BEFORE constructs a mount dentry; new rootid = 2
#   - walk through mount where the name exists in `first` (p2): wins
#   - walk through mount where the name only exists in `second` (p1):
#     fallback after p2 returns NOTFOUND
#   - walk through mount where the name exists ONLY in second arm
#     starting position vs. only in first arm: tests both directions
#   - walk where the name is in neither: NOTFOUND from both arms;
#     final result is the second's notfound dentry
#   - cache hit: repeating the alpha.txt walk returns the same id
vfs register fs {ROOT} p1
vfs register fs {ROOT} p2
vfs bindroot 1 before
vfs walk 2 alpha.txt
vfs open 3
vfs walk 2 only_in_p1.txt
vfs open 5
vfs walk 2 only_in_p2.txt
vfs open 6
vfs walk 2 nowhere.txt
vfs stat 8
vfs walk 2 alpha.txt
